      <scopecontent id="aspace_654e9e43b7c00d86e5ddda480f265622">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection is composed of autographs and letters collected by Eleanor Robson Belmont in connection with a copy of the Treaty of Versailles for which she wanted original signatures. The correspondence in the collection includes cover letters from people who helped her secure the signatures as well as letters from some of the signatories of the Treaty. There is also a small amount of memorabilia.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_29932ec7b6bbb099c5db23926752a7ca">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Eleanor Robson Belmont was born in Lancashire, England in 1879. In 1897, she graduated from St. Peter's Academy, in Staten Island, New York. Upon graduation, Belmont became an actress in California and New York. After her marriage to August Belmont on February 26, 1910, she quit the acting business and focused her attention on philanthropy. Belmont died in 1979.</p>  
      </bioghist>
